result.name: Min Si Fong

reviews.text:
Kennedy Town on the Western edge of HK Island is considered cheap eat area compared to Central.  However with the MTR expanded towards there not long ago, real estate prices and overall prices have steadily gone up.

Came here because they've been around for awhile and well known for their pig's and cow's offals dishes.

At $27 for 3 choices without noodles it was decent.
One of my favorite place for street noodles, soup base simple but tasty, a variety of food to choose from to go with noodles, my favorite is the salted pork.

Traditional cart noodle 車仔麵 at its finest. There's a ton of options you can choose but the one that surprised me the most is actually the pork! Very juicy and tender but it still have a bite.. I guess it's a pork jowl actually. 
And the spirit of the kitchen ladies are very good and positive too. True HK style good food good service in a fairly cheap price, what more do you want?
Good
Noodle quite delicious.

result.name: 麵食坊 (士美非路)

reviews.text: 愛好新鮮豬雜牛雜人士必到😋😋😋
一D都唔好食😡
西環尾最有人氣的車仔麵, 豬牛雜很多部位都有, 豬肉(豬頸肉)亦是其中一絕。爽而不肥膩。芹菜令到成件事很香。

味道不錯, 價錢合理, 車仔麵餸選擇多, 推介牛脷👍真係炇得好冧, 環顧身邊的顧客, 多為老街坊，與員工們打成一片👍 截至今天為止已光顧了两次, 下次途經堅尼地城, 仍會繼續幫襯❗👍😋
牛脷 : 9分
牛腩 : 7分
蘿蔔 : 6分
猪皮 : 5分
麺質 : 6分
湯底 : 5分
堅尼地城地道豬什麵，本土小店，有人情味😊
